<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1243,1916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1423,1448]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a patronym in honour of Anton N. Litvinov (Terekty, 
<collectingCountry box="[1174,1309,1423,1448]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
), the friend of AF, who helped a lot in spider collecting and organization of field trips.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1243,1916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1495,1520]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of the new species differ from those of the similar species 
<taxonomicName box="[1078,1213,1496,1520]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis box="[1078,1213,1496,1520]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">B. koponeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by tegulum bulged prolaterally (
<emphasis box="[301,332,1532,1555]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Bu</emphasis>
), by less curved (as viewed from above) median apophysis, absence of the ridge in embolic division and much longer tibial apophysis (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[680,805,1567,1592]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,202,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19. Habitus and copulatory organs of Berlandina litvinovi sp. n. 9 ‒ 10 female and male habitus, dorsal; 11 ‒ 13 male palp, prolateral, ventral and retrolateral respectively; 14 ‒ 16 bulb, anterior, ventral and retrolateral; 17 intact epigyne, ventral; 18 ‒ 19 macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Figs 11‒16</figureCitation>
and figs 
<quantity box="[912,1012,1567,1592]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.382" metricValueMax="9.144" metricValueMin="7.62" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="33.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="30.0">30‒36 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik" box="[1020,1260,1567,1592]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Fomichev, A. A. &amp; Omelko, M. M. (2014 a) A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa, 3827 (2), 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Marusik 
<emphasis box="[1121,1178,1568,1592]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014a
</bibRefCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litvinovi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">B. litvinovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[253,321,1603,1628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[253,321,1603,1628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to these of 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Logunov" authorityYear="1995" box="[600,1082,1603,1628]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ubsunurica">
<emphasis box="[600,761,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">B. ubsunurica</emphasis>
Marusik &amp; Logunov, 1995
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ponomarev &amp; Tsvetkov, 2006" authorityName="Ponomarev &amp; Tsvetkov" authorityYear="2006" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nenilini">
<emphasis box="[1144,1264,1604,1628]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">B. nenilini</emphasis>
Ponomarev &amp; Tsvetkov, 2006
</taxonomicName>
. They differ from two aforementioned species by wide fovea, less pronounced anterior protrusion on the edge of fovea and by less protruding outgrowths of lateral pockets (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[1012,1137,1675,1700]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,202,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19. Habitus and copulatory organs of Berlandina litvinovi sp. n. 9 ‒ 10 female and male habitus, dorsal; 11 ‒ 13 male palp, prolateral, ventral and retrolateral respectively; 14 ‒ 16 bulb, anterior, ventral and retrolateral; 17 intact epigyne, ventral; 18 ‒ 19 macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Figs 17‒19</figureCitation>
and figs 
<quantity box="[1238,1337,1675,1700]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10‒15 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Fomichev, A. A. &amp; Omelko, M. M. (2014 a) A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa, 3827 (2), 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Marusik 
<emphasis box="[151,208,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014a
</bibRefCitation>
). Both male and female of the new species can be distinguished from the closest species 
<taxonomicName box="[1301,1436,1712,1736]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis box="[1301,1436,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">B. koponeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by dark coloration (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[408,477,1747,1772]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ‒ 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[214,1354,194,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[212,1354,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 ‒ 8. Habitus and epigyne of Berlandina koponeni (1 ‒ 4) and B. nakonechnyi (5 ‒ 8). 1, 5 habitus, dorsal; 2, 7 macerated epigyne, ventral; 3, 6 intact epigyne, ventral; 4, 8 macerated epigyne, dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated. Abbreviation. Op outgrowth of lateral pockets." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569170/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[491,547,1748,1772]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,202,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 ‒ 19. Habitus and copulatory organs of Berlandina litvinovi sp. n. 9 ‒ 10 female and male habitus, dorsal; 11 ‒ 13 male palp, prolateral, ventral and retrolateral respectively; 14 ‒ 16 bulb, anterior, ventral and retrolateral; 17 intact epigyne, ventral; 18 ‒ 19 macerated epigyne, ventral and dorsal. Scale = 0.2 mm if not otherwise indicated." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569171/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">9‒10</figureCitation>
and fig. 
<quantity box="[647,704,1747,1772]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.398" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" unit="in" value="37.0">37 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik" box="[711,948,1747,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Fomichev, A. A. &amp; Omelko, M. M. (2014 a) A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa, 3827 (2), 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014" yearSuffix="a">
Marusik 
<emphasis box="[811,867,1748,1772]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2014a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="4" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1243,1916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1783,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">Description.</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[430,535,1783,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total length 5.4. Carapace: 2.25 long, 1.8 wide. Carapace brown with black margins, spots and radial stripes. Chelicerae and labium dark-brown. Maxillae light-brown. Sternum brown. Legs: femora, patellae and tibiae gray-brown with yellow spots and stripes, metatarsi and tarsi dirty-yellow. Palps yellow-gray. Abdomen gray dorsally with light longitudinal stripe, venter yellow. Spinnerets yellow-gray.
</paragraph>
